{"type":"message","id":"7db00f5d","parentId":"8ce10698","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:46:50.211Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_97pv89yl3ybl_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 094518\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: scripts/tic_analyzer.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n3. The NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n4. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n5. Need to analyze `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define `significance` scoring\r\n- Tune λ empirically\r\n- Wire to TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe most immediate next step based on the Phase 1 Advancement is to implement the TIC classifier on pulse logs.\r\n\r\nSince I'm starting fresh (stateless discontinuous agent), I need to:\r\n1. Check what files exist in the logs directory\r\n2. Implement a TIC classifier\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take. The most immediate next action from the Phase 1 Advancement is to implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nFor a single concrete action, I should:\r\n- Create the TIC experiment implementation\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist. The last pulse mentioned is `pulse_2026-03-24 094322.md`. I need to understand the format of these logs.\r\n\r\nA good concrete action would be to:\r\n1. Create a TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs\r\n2. Or create a research document defining the TIC algorithm\r\n\r\nLet me go with creating the TIC implementation - this advances the Phase 1 goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a unified framework for Phase 1. To validate this hypothesis, I need to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment that classifies pulse log content as invariant vs variant, then predicts subsequent pulses.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs to test the compression-causality hypothesis. This implements the experiment outlined in the Phase 1 Advancement.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\nTest hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n1. Load last 20 pulse logs from `logs/`\r\n2. Extract content vectors for each pulse\r\n3. Classify each content element as:\r\n   - **INVARIANT**: appears consistently across pulses (structure, identity, goals)\r\n   - **VARIANT**: appears sporadically or changes (context, specific content)\r\n4. Predict next pulse from invariant structure\r\n5. Measure accuracy\r\n\r\n## Invariant Categories\r\n- Architecture filenames and relationships\r\n- Goal/phase markers\r\n- File paths referenced repeatedly\r\n- Core concepts (gap, decay, compression, λ)\r\n\r\n## Variant Categories\r\n- Timestamps\r\n- Specific numeric values\r\n- Session-specific observations\r\n- New insights not yet stabilized\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- >70% classification accuracy (invariant vs variant)\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\n## Output\r\nResults saved to `research/TIC-RESULTS.md`\r\n```\r\n\r\nfile: scripts/tic-classifier.ps1\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:45:38\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774360010207}}
